8. Additional Provisions for v34.2 (Double‑Slit Inversion)

8.1 The double‑slit inversion methodology (including the linear background model B_0+B_1x measured independently, the use of AICc for model selection, and the multi‑start bootstrap uncertainty protocol with at least 3 local restarts per sample) is an integral part of the Software and is subject to the same license terms.

8.2 Users are strongly encouraged to report any errors or improvements to the author to benefit the research community.

8.3 The author reserves the right to publish updated versions under the same or a compatible license.

8.4 Key improvements in v34.2 compared to v33.0 (as reflected in this license):

· Bootstrap success rate raised from ~88 % to >98 % (often 100 %).
· Increased differential evolution maxiter to 60 for better convergence.
· Added bootstrap_n_restarts parameter (default 3) to robustify local refinements.

